# Dakboard: Commit and push after every update

When you make changes in this **dakboard** repo, always commit and push to `main` when the updates are done—unless the user explicitly says not to.

## Remote

- **Repository:** https://github.com/sidmsmith/dakboard
- **Branch:** `main`

## Steps (final step after completing edits)

1. `cd` to the dakboard repo root (this directory).
2. `git status` and `git diff` — stage only files related to your changes (not unrelated build artifacts or secrets like `config.js`).
3. `git commit -m "..."` with a clear message focused on **why**.
4. `git push origin main`.

Do this after every update batch, not only when the user asks.
